main event: Multiple sightings of unusual bright lights observed at Keflavik Airport on 3/19/53.
interesting points: The lights were described as bright, round, and stationary., The sightings were visual observations only with no physical evidence., There were radar plots observed on 3 February 1953 that indicated unidentified objects in the area., The radar plots included high-speed targets moving at an altitude of around 25,000 feet., Local aircraft from the Icelandic Air Force were not in the air at the time of the sightings.
